# Secrets, Release gates, and logging

Source: **`owasp_access_control_policy.md`** (§2.6–2.7, §5), **`owasp_secrets_handling.md`** (Phase 3).

## Secrets

- Keep Maps / Fishial / CDN / **`GoogleService-Info.plist`** **gitignored**; only commit **`.example`** templates (`YOUR_*` placeholders).
- Treat anything in the IPA as **extractable**. Maps: restrict key to iOS + **`PrimoSoftware.GoDiveMVP`**. Fishial: **client secret is in-IPA until a proxy** — never log tokens / `Authorization` / `client_secret` (use **`GoDiveSecretLogging`** if describing headers).
- **`GoogleService-Info`** is expected Firebase **client config** (still gitignored) — not a vault secret.
- Prefer restricted keys / short-lived tokens / future Fishial Cloud Function + App Check over new long-lived client secrets.
- **Do not** add TLS certificate pinning or Firebase App Check unless the user scopes that work (documented follow-ups).

## Release gates (do not regress)

| Gate | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Mock seed | **`MockDataSeeding.isLaunchSeedingEnabled`** stays **`false`** for ship |
| UITest | **`GoDiveUITestRootView`** only when **`-GoDiveUITest`** / env set |
| ATS | No **`NSAppTransportSecurity`** / **`NSAllowsArbitraryLoads`** without documented review (**`AppTransportSecurityPolicy`**) |
| Crash share | Opt-in only; scrub with **`CrashReportPayloadScrubber`** before public CloudKit upload; do not default-on |
| Hybrid | No dive-log models written to Firebase (see **`godive-hybrid-trust-boundaries.mdc`**) |
| CDN | SHA-256 fail-closed; HTTPS-only base; **`catalog/v1/`** paths |
| Diagnostics backup | Exclude CloudKit open dump + diagnostics store family from device backups |

## Logging / errors

- Prefer **`Logger`** with privacy-aware interpolation; avoid **`print`** for auth/network failures.
- Do not use **`.public`** for UIDs, emails, tokens, GPS, site names, or dive notes in Release-facing logs.
- User-facing auth / social errors: **generic** copy (no credential enumeration).

## Session storage

- Non-sensitive prefs may stay in UserDefaults / synced **`UserPreferences`**.
- Session restore / returning hints / Firebase UID: **Keychain** via **`GoDiveKeychainStore`** (see **`godive-session-keychain.mdc`**).

## Deferred (see `cursor/todo.md`)

Fishial Cloud Function proxy → Firebase App Check → signed CDN manifests → TLS pinning — do not block Phases 4–6.
